messages.content: Meta: Llama 4 Maverick 和Meta: Llama 4 Scout 两个模型的区别

As of July 16, 2025, Meta's Llama 4 family of AI models includes Llama 4 Scout and Llama 4 Maverick, both launched on April 5, 2025 [usthadian](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1]. These models leverage a mixture-of-experts (MoE) architecture and native multimodality [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [techtarget](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [ibm](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [deploy](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [bdtechtalks](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7) [datastudios](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [gocodeo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10) [groq](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-11). Here's a comparison of the two:

**1. Architecture and Parameters:**

*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Has 17 billion active parameters within a total of approximately 109 billion parameters, utilizing 16 experts [getbind](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [artificialanalysis](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11) [oracle](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12) [dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [bdtechtalks](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [gocodeo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). It is a full MoE consisting of 16 experts, where all FFN layers are MoE [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13). It uses coarse-grained experts [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18).
*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Also has 17 billion active parameters but within a larger total of about 400 billion parameters, employing 128 experts [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8) [oracle](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) [getbind](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [openrouter](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7) [bdtechtalks](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [gocodeo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9). MoE and dense layers alternate, so experts are applied in only half of the layers [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-15) [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13]. Each MoE layer comprises 128 routed experts and one shared expert, with each token activating the shared expert and one routed expert [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-15) [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). It uses fine-grained experts [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18).

**2. Context Length:**

*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Supports a context length of up to 10 million tokens [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8) [getbind](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [gocodeo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10) [dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [deploy](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7) [datastudios](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8).
*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Supports a context length of 1 million tokens [getbind](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [artificialanalysis](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-15) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [openrouter](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [deploy](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).

**3. Positional Embeddings:**

*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Employs an Interleaved RoPE (iRoPE) approach, combining RoPE and NoPE (No Position Encoding) layers, to handle ultra-long contexts [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-12). NoPE layers are used every 4 layers [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).
*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Does not use iRoPE [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-12) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9).

**4. Capabilities and Intended Use:**

*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Excels in tasks requiring long-context processing, such as summarizing entire books or analyzing massive codebases [getbind](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [coditude](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-14) [datastudios](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8). It is designed for long workflows and massive data analysis [datastudios](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8). It is optimized for speed and cost [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13).
*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Excels in conversational and creative functions [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) and is optimized for vision-language tasks [openrouter](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7). It strikes a balance between reasoning power and response speed [datastudios](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8). It is designed for advanced reasoning, multilingual capabilities, multimodal tasks, and code generation [gocodeo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10).

**5. Performance and Cost:**

*   Llama 4 Maverick generally outperforms Llama 4 Scout on benchmarks like ChartQA, GPQA, LiveCodeBench, MATH, MBPP, MGSM, MMLU, MMLU-Pro, MMMU, MathVista, and TydiQA [llm-stats](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-13).
*   Llama 4 Maverick is more expensive: Input tokens cost $0.17/1M, and output tokens cost $0.60/1M, compared to Llama 4 Scout's $0.08/1M for input and $0.30/1M for output [llm-stats](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-13) [openrouter](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6).

**6. Training:**

*   Both Llama 4 Maverick and Scout were trained using Llama 4 Behemoth as a teacher [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18). Llama 4 Maverick was co-distilled from Llama 4 Behemoth, using a novel loss function that dynamically weights the student and teacher logit [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18).

In summary, Llama 4 Scout is designed for tasks requiring extremely long context windows and is optimized for cost and speed, while Llama 4 Maverick is designed for more general-purpose tasks, balancing reasoning, multimodality, and creative capabilities, albeit at a higher cost [datastudios](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8).

This MoE approach involves a collection of specialized "expert" networks and a routing mechanism that selectively activates a subset of parameters for each input token [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [ibm](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-12) [dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13) [bdtechtalks](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). This design allows for a massive total parameter count while keeping the active parameters per inference manageable [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-14). Both models also leverage early fusion for native multimodality, enabling them to process text and image inputs [bdtechtalks](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [ibm](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-15) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13) [dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6).

Here's a breakdown of the architectural differences between Llama 4 Scout and Llama 4 Maverick:

**1. Expert Count and Parameter Size:**

*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Features 16 experts with 17 billion active parameters and 109 billion total parameters [dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [bdtechtalks](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [gocodeo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).
*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Employs 128 experts, also with 17 billion active parameters, but has a significantly larger total parameter count of 400 billion [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7) [bdtechtalks](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [gocodeo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9).

The difference in the number of experts suggests different design philosophies [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-17). Scout may favor a broader distribution of expertise across a smaller set of more generalist experts, while Maverick's larger pool allows for finer-grained specialization [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-17).

**2. MoE Layer Implementation:**

*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Is a full MoE consisting of 16 experts [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4). All FFN layers are MoE [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13).
*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Uses 128 experts, but MoE and dense layers alternate [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-15) [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13). Therefore, experts are applied in only half of the layers [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4). Each MoE layer comprises 128 routed experts and one shared expert [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-15) [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). Each token activates the shared expert and one of the 128 routed experts [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).

**3. Context Length:**

*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Has an industry-leading context length of 10 million tokens [gocodeo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10) [dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [deploy](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7) [datastudios](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8). It is pre-trained and post-trained with a 256K context length [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).
*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Supports a 1 million token context length [deploy](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2) [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4). It is pre-trained with a context length of 256K [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).

**4. Positional Embeddings:**

*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Employs an Interleaved RoPE (iRoPE) approach, combining RoPE and NoPE (No Position Encoding) layers, to handle ultra-long contexts [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-12). NoPE layers are used every 4 layers [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).
*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Does not use iRoPE [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-12) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9).

**5. Expert Granularity:**

*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Uses coarse-grained experts [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18).
*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Uses fine-grained experts [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18).

**6. Intended Use and Performance:**

*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Designed for long workflows and massive data analysis [datastudios](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8). It excels in tasks like long-document summarization, multi-file coding, forensic analysis, data verification, and content generation requiring maximum memory in the prompt [datastudios](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8). It is optimized for speed and cost [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13).
*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Strikes a balance between reasoning power and response speed [datastudios](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8). It is designed for advanced reasoning, multilingual capabilities, multimodal tasks, and code generation [gocodeo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10). It is better suited for general-purpose AI assistants, chatbots, creative content generation, and tasks that require a strong balance of performance across various modalities, including robust coding and reasoning capabilities [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-17).

**7. Routing Mechanism and Expert Selection:**

Both Llama 4 Scout and Maverick utilize a routing mechanism to determine which experts are activated for a given token [dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-14) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9) [bdtechtalks](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13) [ibm](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-12) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). The routing mechanism involves computing routing probabilities and selecting the top-k experts [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-19) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). Llama 4 models, relative to other popular MoEs, have a very small number of active parameters [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18).

*   **Router:** The router decides which experts get activated for a given token [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13). The choice of the routing mechanism plays a central role in the model's performance [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13).
*   **Router Affinity Score:** A token is sent to the routed expert with the highest router score, and the activations of the token are also multiplied with the router affinity score [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13).

**8. Shared Expert:**

Both Llama 4 Maverick and Scout models use both shared and routed experts [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [bdtechtalks](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-15) [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18) [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7). All tokens are passed to the shared expert [deeplearning](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-13) [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18) [medium](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-15) [bdtechtalks](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [meta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-16) [collabnix](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).

**9. Training and Distillation:**

*   **Llama 4 Maverick:** Was co-distilled from a larger model, Llama 4 Behemoth, using a novel loss function that dynamically weights the student and teacher logit [huggingface](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18).
*   **Llama 4 Scout:** Was also trained using the Behemoth model as a teacher [substack](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-18).
